President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2012 as National Physical Fitness and Sports Month. He emphasizes the importance of leading an active and healthy lifestyle, as it promotes physical and mental development, prevents chronic diseases, and maintains a healthy weight. The Obama administration, through initiatives such as Let's Move! and the President's Council on Fitness, Sports, and Nutrition, aims to provide Americans with the tools and information necessary to maintain a healthy lifestyle. The government is working to ensure children have access to nutritious food and to encourage physical activity in schools and communities. President Obama calls upon the people of the United States to prioritize daily physical activity, sports participation, and good nutrition in their lives.